    "Figure 1 demonstrates the evaluation of debridement effects.",
    "Specifically, debridement is anticipated to improve blood circulation to the area of the DFU, thereby increasing the local temperature.",
    "This temperature change can be quantitatively assessed through thermal imaging.",
    "Prior to debridement, the wound is likely to exhibit a lower temperature due to the presence of necrotic tissue, which typically has poor blood supply.",
    "After debridement, a temperature rise is expected as a result of the acute inflammatory response, which is characterized by localized bleeding and inflammation."
